| `digest-gateway.ts` | policy | Digest composition and digest action behavior move. It composes and executes digest decisions (`:159-267`) and owns digest callbacks (`:310-464`). |
| `discord-ui/components/approval-card.ts`, `discovery-card.ts`, `heartbeat-digest.ts`, `mcq-flow.ts`, `run-card.ts`, `search-result-card.ts`, `session-card.ts`, `status-container.ts` | policy | Fixed operator-facing presentation profiles move to the agent. |
| `discord-ui/helpers/accent-color.ts`, `helpers/format.ts`, `helpers/truncate.ts`, `discord-ui/index.ts`, `discord-ui/slash-commands/handler.ts` | policy | Visual tone, truncation, formatting, exports, and command response choices move with the UI policy. |
| `formatting/cli.ts`, `formatting/discord.ts`, `formatting/imessage.ts`, `formatting/telegram.ts`, `formatting/index.ts` | policy | These inject channel-specific prompt instructions. The new agent owns rewrite and format choice. Transport keeps only platform-safe encoding. |
| `guardrails.ts` | policy | Tool budgets and deploy verification rules belong to the agent runtime, not transport (`:3-79`). |
| `heartbeat.ts` | policy | This prompts the old gateway session and filters its answer (`startHeartbeatRunner`, `:218`). Replace it with the new container heartbeat contract; do not keep it as transport policy. |
| `knowledge-turn.ts` | policy | Gateway knowledge-write decisions belong to the agent and its stream memory (`:98-237`). |
| `lib/pi-process-pool.ts` | policy | Old Pi inference workers move or retire with the old in-process agent runtime (`createPiProcessPool`, `:46`). |
| `lib/thread-tracker.ts` | policy | Conversation summaries and lifecycle memory move to the agent/stream model. Transport keeps only platform IDs and origin correlation. |
| `maintenance-policy.ts` | policy | Compaction/rotation decisions move to the agent container lifecycle (`decideIdleGatewayMaintenance`, `:20`). |
| `operator-relay.ts` | policy | This is the clearest policy blob: it scores signals, chooses immediate/batched/suppressed/ingested, and authors digest guidance (`:119-121,371-479`). Move it; do not wrap it. |
| `outbound/format.ts` | policy | It rewrites text and injects Telegram style rules (`:36-53`). The gateway agent owns this. |
| `outbound/router.ts` | policy | It selects a channel from source/context, applies formatting, suppresses heartbeat output, and routes the old session response (`:145-239`). Replace with an explicit agent-to-transport send request. |
| `session-pressure.ts` | policy | Context compaction/rotation policy moves to the agent container (`:54-155`). |
| `telegram-outbound-policy.ts` | policy | Move the whole decision layer: deliver/digest/suppress/investigate, digest queueing, and suppression journal (`:160-393`). Do not call it from fallback. |

## `packages/gateway/src`: seams that change shape

| File | Classification | Current mix and target shape |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `daemon.ts` | seam | It composes the old agent, channels, policy, Redis, Chat SDK, health, and legacy outbound queue. Chat SDK startup is at `:4982`; notify transport ingress is at `:5130-5450`. Split into a small transport composition root plus the separate gateway-agent container. |
| `channels/types.ts` | seam | `SendOptions` mixes mechanics (`replyTo`, media, audit) with policy (`format`, `silent`, `noPreview`, `outboundPolicy`) at `:14-24`. Keep mechanical fields. Replace policy fields with an agent-authored postable payload and explicit fallback marker. |
| `channels/redis.ts` | seam | Keeps Redis ingress/replay mechanics, but removes triage, batching, suppression, digest prompts, and old-agent enqueue. Current policy starts immediately after notify compatibility at `:795-906`; digest assembly is `:1296-1355`. The replacement appends to the message stream and invokes fallback only on stale agent heartbeat. |
| `chat-sdk/index.ts` | seam | Public exports must separate transport API from compatibility and policy APIs. |
| `chat-sdk/notify-compat.ts` | seam | Keep a temporary producer compatibility decoder. Remove source inference and routing authority. Its output becomes a facts/origin stream record, not an `OutboundIntent` whose kind selects a route. |
| `chat-sdk/notify-acting.ts` | seam | Keep envelope recognition, terminal error handling, and compatibility telemetry. Replace direct contract-v2 policy delivery (`routeNotifySendCompat`, `:168-214`) with stream append plus terminal receipt lookup. |
| `chat-sdk/outbound.ts` | seam | This is the current `send()` boundary (`makeOutboundSender`, `:536`; singleton `send`, `:813`). Keep adapters, target lookup, reply anchors, journaling, platform send, and receipts. Remove `resolveMessageRoute`, `ROUTING_TABLE_V2`, `TelegramPolicyPort`, kind-derived platform choice, and suppression/digest terminal states (`:539-709`). The agent must pass an explicit target, postable content, origin/flow IDs, and delivery intent. |
| `chat-sdk-inbound/acting.ts` | seam | Keep Chat SDK handler registration, actor verification, normalization, dedupe, and correlation. Remove `dispatchPlatformPolicy`, `prepareInvoke`, and direct old-session enqueue (`:35-79,232-390`). Publish every accepted inbound event to the stream with its origin/flow references. |
| `chat-sdk-inbound/normalize.ts` | seam | Platform normalization keeps. Embedded `InboundAuthorization.policyAction` and execution decisions must shrink to mechanical actor/auth facts; the agent interprets intent (`normalizeSdkInboundEvent`, `:621`). |
| `chat-sdk-inbound/publish.ts` | seam | Bus publication keeps (`createGatewayInboundBusClient`, `:41`). Replace the observe-only/shadow contract with canonical stream append and a durable append receipt (`:63-89`). |
| `slack-runtime.ts` | seam | Keep Slack send, socket/runtime state, and normalized events. Move reply grants, mention routing, passive-intel policy, and direct agent enqueue (`:742-1080`). |
| `telegram-runtime.ts` | seam | Keep Bot API mechanics, chunking, editing, callbacks, receipts, and platform formatting fallback. Remove `routeTelegramOutbound` preflight (`:1574-1597,1971-1985`) and direct old-session enqueue (`:918-1153`). Add a narrow raw-text fallback send that bypasses policy and rich formatting. |
| `telegram-stream.ts` | seam | Keep transport streaming/edit mechanics only if the new agent needs them. Remove policy resolution and suppression (`:212-252,592-616`). Stream delivery must start from an explicit agent send request. |
| `watchdog.ts` | seam | Existing code detects dead old sessions after failures (`:1-35`). Replace its input with the gateway-agent container heartbeat/staleness signal. Keep the external watcher role and grace timing. |
| `outbound/envelope.ts` | seam | Replace the old channel/format envelope with an explicit agent-authored transport request plus origin, flow, reply, and audit fields (`:3-21`). |

