## Tests under `packages/gateway/src`

Tests inherit their production classification. Preserve transport proofs, rewrite seam proofs, and move policy proofs with the agent:

- **Transport tests keep:** `callback-trace.test.ts`, `channel-health.test.ts`, `channels/error-emission-budget.test.ts`, `message-journal.test.ts`, `telegram-markdown.test.ts`.
- **Policy tests move:** `commands/config.test.ts`, `digest-gateway.test.ts`, `guardrails.test.ts`, `heartbeat.test.ts`, `knowledge-turn.test.ts`, `maintenance-policy.test.ts`, `operator-relay.test.ts`, `session-pressure.test.ts`, `telegram-outbound-policy.test.ts`.
- **Seam tests change:** `chat-sdk-inbound/acting.test.ts`, `chat-sdk-inbound/cutover.e2e.test.ts`, `chat-sdk-inbound/inbound.test.ts`, `chat-sdk/__tests__/notify-acting.test.ts`, `chat-sdk/__tests__/outbound.test.ts`, `chat-sdk/__tests__/visible-delivery-canary.test.ts`, `command-queue.test.ts`, `slack-runtime.test.ts`, `telegram-runtime.test.ts`, `telegram-stream.test.ts`, `watchdog.test.ts`.

The new seam suite needs four end-to-end proofs: producer append, agent-authored send, inbound reply/reaction correlation, and stale-heartbeat raw fallback.

